revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page and interwikis go in Wikidata. -->
This template provides a list of links to a template. There are no restricted links (such as adding protection to the template). A link to a related module can be added.
== Usage ==
* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{t links|infobox building}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;<br>{{t links|infobox building}}

* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{t links|infobox building|sandboxlinks=yes}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;<br>{{t links|infobox building|sandboxlinks=yes}}
::<small>(same effect:)</small>
* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{t links|infobox building/sandbox}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;<br>{{t links|infobox building/sandbox}}

== Options ==

;Adding link to a module:
When an eponymous module exists, it is added:
* {{tlc|T links|Track gauge}} &rarr;

::{{T links|Track gauge|module=Track gauge}}<!-- /docpage construct -->

* Any other module (or none) can be linked:

* {{tlc|T links|Track gauge|module=String}} &rarr;

::{{T links|Track gauge|module=string}}

* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{T links|Track gauge|module=}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;

::{{T links|Track gauge|module=}} (blank so not linked)

;Adding sandbox links:
When working with the <code>../sandbox</code> of templates, the sandbox links can be made explicit:
* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{T links|Track gauge|sandboxlinks=yes}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;
::{{T links|Track gauge|sandboxlinks=yes}}
:This can also help to prevent changing the live version code by accident.

;Adding the [[WP:TPU]]-link:
* {{code|1=<nowiki>{{T links|Track gauge|tpu=yes}}</nowiki>}} &rarr;
::{{T links|Track gauge|tpu=yes}}

== See also ==
* {{tl|T links/sandbox links}} used when adding, eg by  {{para|sandboxlinks|yes}}
*{{tl|m links}}, a similar template producing module-related links.

{{Template-linking templates}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other|
| <!-- Categories go here, and interwikis go in Wikidata -->
[[Category:Internal template-link templates]]
[[Category:Templates using Toolforge]]
}}</includeonly>

